HEADWORD: Whitten tree
<hw>Whit"ten tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Probably from
<ets>white</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>hwitingtre⟦oacute⟧w</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Either of two shrubs (<spn>Viburnum
Lantana</spn>, and <spn>Viburnum Opulus</spn>), so called on account of
their whitish branches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whitterick</ent>⟦br⟧
